line_1: No: view me firm, unshaken, undismay'd,
line_2: As when the welcome mandate I obey'd —

line_1: Unmov'd in toils, in dangers undismay'd,
line_2: From fiercest monsters, thro' her pow'rful aid,

line_1: Of the dread future, calm and undismay'd,
line_2: Till I may claim the Hope — that shall not fade!

line_1: The brinded boars may slumber un-dismay'd,
line_2: Or grunt secure beneath the chesnut shade.

line_1: Or firm thro' Him and undismay'd,
line_2: Sharp as the Thorns that tore his Head,

line_1: His trusty warriors, few, but undismay'd;
line_2: He said, and, on the rampart-heights, array'd

line_1: To meet the threats Boreas undismay'd,
line_2: And Winter's gathering frowns and hoary head.
Views the long sword and fierce cockade.
Give me in all thy Paths to tread.
